description:
Amish RENOgades - Season 1, Episode 7

Backyard Ranch Oasis
Albert and Leon deal with extreme cold while on a ranch in Texas, where they are turning a rundown patio into a dream backyard. Projects include using material from an 80-year-old barn to make a pergola, constructing a full outdoor kitchen and rebuilding a fire pit. Also: The guys learn how to rope like a cowboy and enter a barbecue-eating contest.

Original Air Date: 07-Mar-2015


Amish RENOgades - Season 1, Episode 8

A Bathroom Oasis by the Big Apple
A major bathroom renovation brings the guys to New York, where they create a contemporary spa-like oasis, complete with a sleek tile design, cedar ceilings and an Amish-made vanity. Also: Albert and Leon find time to ride the subway, explore Times Square and try Indian food for the first time.

Original Air Date: 07-Mar-2015


Amish RENOgades - Season 1, Episode 9

A Fix Fit for Christmas
Albert and Leo work to make a December 25 deadline when they travel to Staten Island to redo a conjoined dining room and living room. The project includes custom built-ins and furniture, repurposing old wood floors and metal leaf painting. Also: The guys take a ferry ride, visit Chinatown and experience Christmastime in the Big Apple.

Original Air Date: 14-Mar-2015
